http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 28 May 2021
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=33907


Infectious hematopoietic necrosis, Finland
------------------------------------------
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 24 May 2021
Confirmed: 27 May 2021
Reported: 28 May 2021
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence in a zone or a compartment
Causal agent: infectious haematopoietic necrosis [IHN] virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks (1)
Outbreak location 1: Foglo, Aland
Started: 24 May 2021
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected: [Note: Quantitative data for affected animals was not provided. The disease was diagnosed in a Rainbow trout farm (_Oncorhynchus mykiss_). - Mod.CRD]

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: legal movement of animals

Epidemiological comments: The outbreak resulted from legal movement of live fish from a farm in another EU member state, which was reported IHN positive after the movement. The infected farm is under restrictions and will be emptied as soon as practically possible. The farm is only producing fish for slaughter and has not moved fish to any other farm in Finland or other countries. A 10-km [0.6 mile] restriction zone in accordance with EU legislation has been established around the outbreak, and all other farms in the restriction zone will be tested. The farm is located in a region of Finland (Aland) that is only producing fish for slaughter and cannot move fish to other parts of Finland, because of a different status for VHS.

Control measures at event level:
Domestic control measures applied: traceability; selective killing and disposal; surveillance within infected and/or protection zone; surveillance outside infected and/or protection zone; process to inactivate the pathogenic agent in products or by-products; movement control inside the country.

Domestic control measures to be applied: zoning; selective killing and disposal; killing for commercial use or own use; disinfection.

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Outbreaks / Test / Test date / Result
Finnish Food Authority National Laboratory / Rainbow trout / Rainbow trout / 1 / Real-time polymerase chain reaction (real-time PCR) / 26 May 2021 / positive
Finnish Food Authority National Laboratory / Rainbow trout / Rainbow trout / 1 / Reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 26 May 2021 / positive
Finnish Food Authority National Laboratory / Rainbow trout / Rainbow trout / 1 / Gene sequencing / 27 May 2021 / positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

